IBADAN – As the 2023 general elections draws nearer, the Alaafin of Oyo, Oba Lamidi Adeyemi III and Ooni of Ife, Oba Adeyeye Enitan Ogunwusi, Ojaja II have encouraged the member House of Representatives, Hon Shina Peller with the responsibility of ensuring that peaceful co-existence exist among all tribes across the country. Besides, the royal fathers also charged the Ayedero (one who brings peace and prosperity) of Yorubaland to harness the potentials of all Nigerian youths in finding solutions to the spate of insecurity in the country. Alaafin, who installed Hon Shina Peller as Ayedero of Yorubaland last year, saddled Peller with the responsibility in his Palace as Peller paid homage to the monarch on his 51st coronation and to seek royal blessings to perform the responsibility as the Ayedero of Yorubaland. Kanu: IPOB, Urges Ndigbo To Storm Umuahia High Court On… Dangote, Emefiele Commend Ogun As Investment-Friendly Alaafin said the title bestowed on Peller has given him (Peller) the mandate to move around the country to find ways in bringing youths together to channel their potentials into the peaceful co-existence of every tribe in the country for the development of the country. The first-class monarch, while giving the royal blessing on the responsibility, said he would give his staff of office to follow Peller to wherever he intends to go to solicit for peaceful co-existence ahead of the 2023 general elections.